saṃyutta nikāya 19
2. dutiyavagga
14. maṅgulitthisutta
# NOTE: BB has “ugly”, following comm. But mangula appears in MN 36, where the corresponding Sanskrit term in Lal 17 is madgura. This is a kind of fish or the caste of those who fish them. Fishwife seems to suit.
“idhāhaṃ, āvuso, gijjhakūṭā pabbatā orohanto addasaṃ itthiṃ duggandhaṃ maṅguliṃ vehāsaṃ gacchantiṃ.
tamenaṃ gijjhāpi kākāpi kulalāpi anupatitvā anupatitvā vitacchenti virājenti.
sā sudaṃ aṭṭassaraṃ karoti … pe …
esā, bhikkhave, itthī imasmiṃyeva rājagahe ikkhaṇikā ahosi … pe ….
catutthaṃ.
